t_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58964</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Down Creighton to Advance to Crown Championship Game</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/4/mens-basketball-mountaineers-down-creighton-to-advance-to-crown-championship-game</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/4/mens-basketball-mountaineers-down-creighton-to-advance-to-crown-championship-game</guid><category>Men's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Chance Moore" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/4/Moore-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />Freshman DJ Thomas' 20 points led five double-figure scorers in West Virginia's 87-70 victory over Creighton at T-Mobile Arena in Las Vegas, to advance to tomorrow's championship game of the College Basketball Crown.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/4/Moore-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/4/Moore-Main.jpg"><media:title>Chance Moore</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/4/Moore-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 4 Apr 2026 18:40:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>4</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58963</s:story_id></item><item><title>WVU Tennis Falls at No. 37 Kansas</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/4/wvu-tennis-falls-at-no-37-kansas</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/4/wvu-tennis-falls-at-no-37-kansas</guid><category>Tennis</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tennis Team" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/4/BBD01120.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University tennis team dropped a 4-0 decision at No. 37 Kansas on Friday afternoon at the Jayhawk Tennis Center.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/4/BBD01120.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/4/BBD01120.jpg"><media:title>Tennis Team</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/4/BBD01120.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 4 Apr 2026 00:17:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>15</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58962</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Drop Series Opener to UCF</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/3/baseball-mountaineers-drop-series-opener-to-ucf</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/3/baseball-mountaineers-drop-series-opener-to-ucf</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Dawson Montesa" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/3/4-35-3.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 13 West Virginia University baseball team dropped its series opener against No. 23 UCF, 5-0, Friday night at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers fall to 20-6 and 7-3 in the Big 12 while the Knights improve to 19-8 and 9-1 in conference play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/3/4-35-3.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/3/4-35-3.jpg"><media:title>Dawson Montesa</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/3/4-35-3.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 3 Apr 2026 22:34:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58961</s:story_id></item><item><title>Saturday's Baseball Game Against UCF Moved Up</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/3/saturdays-baseball-game-against-ucf-moved-up</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/3/saturdays-baseball-game-against-ucf-moved-up</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Baseball Hat and Glove " src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2024/3/7/DSC00440.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Due to forecasted inclement weather, the baseball game between West Virginia and UCF on Saturday, April 4, has been moved up to 2 p.m. ET.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2024/3/7/DSC00440.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2024/3/7/DSC00440.jpg"><media:title>Baseball Hat and Glove </media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2024/3/7/DSC00440.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 3 Apr 2026 13:30:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58960</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Extend Season With Victory Over Stanford</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/3/mens-basketball-mountaineers-extend-season-with-victory-over-stanford</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/3/mens-basketball-mountaineers-extend-season-with-victory-over-stanford</guid><category>Men's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Ross Hodge" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/3/Hodge-Team.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia held Stanford to just one basket over the final 3:21 of regulation and then outscored the Cardinal 14-9 in overtime to advance to the semifinals of the College Basketball Crown in Las Vegas to face Creighton on Saturday afternoon.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/3/Hodge-Team.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/3/Hodge-Team.jpg"><media:title>Ross Hodge</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/3/Hodge-Team.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 3 Apr 2026 10:14:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>4</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58959</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Rally to Down Stanford in College Basketball Crown Quarterfinals in Las Vegas</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/2/mens-basketball-mountaineers-rally-to-down-stanford-in-college-basketball-crown-quarterfinals-in-las-vegas</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/2/mens-basketball-mountaineers-rally-to-down-stanford-in-college-basketball-crown-quarterfinals-in-las-vegas</guid><category>Men's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Morris Ugusuk" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Crown-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />West Virginia rallied from eight points down with 3:21 left in regulation, and then outscored Stanford 14-9 in the extra session to claim tonight's first quarterfinal-round game 82-77 in the 2026 College Basketball Crown played at MGM Grand Garden Arena in Las Vegas.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Crown-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Crown-Main.jpg"><media:title>Morris Ugusuk</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Crown-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 2 Apr 2026 23:10:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>4</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58958</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia’s Individuals Complete NCAA Regional Competition</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/2/gymnastics-west-virginias-individuals-complete-ncaa-regional-competition</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/2/gymnastics-west-virginias-individuals-complete-ncaa-regional-competition</guid><category>Gymnastics</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="emerson smith" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Untitled-1-6.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Junior Amber Lowe and sophomores Sophia Rice and Emerson Smith of the West Virginia University gymnastics team completed competition as individual event specialists in the Second Round of the NCAA Regional Championships inside the Maravich Center in Baton Rouge, Louisiana, on Thursday night.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Untitled-1-6.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Untitled-1-6.jpg"><media:title>emerson smith</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Untitled-1-6.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 2 Apr 2026 22:33:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>11</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58957</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Host No. 23 UCF in Battle for First Place</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/2/baseball-mountaineers-host-no-23-ucf-in-battle-for-first-place</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/2/baseball-mountaineers-host-no-23-ucf-in-battle-for-first-place</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="BSB vs UCF 2026" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/2/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_UCF.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – After finishing a 4-1 road trip, the No. 13 West Virginia University baseball team returns home for a weekend series against first place and No. 23 UCF at Kendrick Family Ballpark. First pitch on Friday is set for 6:30 p.m., Saturday for 4 p.m., and Sunday for noon.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_UCF.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_UCF.jpg"><media:title>BSB vs UCF 2026</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_UCF.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 2 Apr 2026 16:09:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58956</s:story_id></item><item><title>WVU Heads to Fairfax for Dalton Ebanks Invitational</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/2/track-field-wvu-heads-to-fairfax-for-dalton-ebanks-invitational</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/2/track-field-wvu-heads-to-fairfax-for-dalton-ebanks-invitational</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Sierra Heisey" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/2/JLS_6445.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University track and field team travels to Fairfax, Virginia, for the Dalton Ebanks Invitational, hosted by George Mason, on April 3-4.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/JLS_6445.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/JLS_6445.jpg"><media:title>Sierra Heisey</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/JLS_6445.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 2 Apr 2026 14:42:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58955</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>